{
  "text": "Short CGG repeats were shown to form a duplex structure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and in the presence of potassium ions-G-tetraplexes [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Thus, an RNA structure formed by CGG repeats is less clearly defined than in the case of CUG repeats [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] and CAG repeats [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] for which crystal structures have been determined [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] [CITATION_15] .",
